article.headline: Idaho State 88, Boise State 79
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho (AP) -- Junior guard David Schroeder scored 19 points and Casey Winters blocked a career-high six shots Thursday night as Idaho State held off Boise State 88-79. Idaho State (3-1, 0-0 Big Sky) led by as many as 14 points in the second half, taking a 59-45 lead with 11:19 remaining on Logan Kinghorn's lay-up. The Broncos (2-2, 0-0 Western Athletic Conference) slowly chipped away at the deficit and cut the lead to just one, at 72-71, with 3:23 remaining in the game when junior guard Coby Karl nailed a jumper. Then Idaho State went on a 7-0 run, led by five points from Tim Henry and a crowd-pleasing one-handed alley-oop dunk by senior Slim Millien. In addition to his six blocks, Winters scored 13 points. Henry had 17 and Kinghorn scored 16. Karl, the son of Denver Nuggets coach George Karl, led all scorers with 21 points for Boise State. Matt Bauscher had 16 points for the Broncos, and junior guard Kenny Wilson had 12.
